An '''icosahedral number''' is a [[figurate number]] that represents an [[icosahedron]]. The ''n''th icosahedral number is given by the formula

:<math>{n(5n^2-5n+2) \over 2}</math>

The first such numbers are 1, 12, 48, 124, 255, 456, 742, 1128, 1629, 2260, 3036, 3972, 5083, … {{OEIS|id=A006564}}.

